    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1961-04-19T13:57:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1961-04-19T13:57:00-05:00" n="152"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d152">
                <head>152. Telegram From the Commander of Special Task Group 81.8 (<persName
                        corresp="#p_CRAJE1" type="from">Clark</persName>) to the Commander in Chief,
                    Atlantic (<persName corresp="#p_DARL1" type="to">Dennison</persName>)<note n="0"
                        type="source" xml:id="d152fn0">Source: Naval Historical Center, Area Files,
                        Bumpy Road Materials. Top Secret; Emergency; Exclusive. Repeated to <gloss
                            target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss>,<gloss target="#t_COMCARIBSEAFRON1"
                            >COMCARIBSEAFRON</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_COMKWESTFOR1"
                            >COMKWESTFOR</gloss>, and COMNAVBASE <gloss target="#t_GTMO1"
                            >GTMO</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <gloss target="#t_USS1">USS</gloss>
                            <hi rend="italic">Essex</hi>, Caribbean</placeName>, <date
                            calendar="gregorian" when="1961-04-19T13:57:00">April 19, 1961, 1:57
                            p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>191857Z. Bumpy Road. Exclusive for <persName corresp="#p_DARL1"
                        >Dennison</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_GMGDW1">Gray</persName>,
                        <persName corresp="#p_SBK1">Smith</persName>, McElroy, OʼDonnell from
                        <persName corresp="#p_CRAJE1">Clark</persName>. Bumpy Road.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>AD-5W unable track <persName corresp="#p_CRF1">Castro</persName> aircraft
                        to and from bases. Observed unidentified jet following my returning <gloss
                            target="#t_CAP1">CAP</gloss> to seaward for about 20 miles then
                        returning.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CRF1">Castro</persName> B-26 orbiting over beach,
                        probably gun spotter. I am initiating air to air combat over beach
                            area.<note n="1" xml:id="d152fn1">In response to this message, <persName
                                corresp="#p_DARL1">Dennison</persName> sent an order at 2:16 p.m. to
                            the Commander of the air unit based at Key West, and the Commander of
                            the naval base at Guantanamo: “Be prepared provide fighter assistance to
                                <gloss target="#t_CTG1">CTG</gloss> 81.8 on his request.” (<gloss
                                target="#t_CINCLANTFLT1">CINCLANTFLT</gloss> telegram 191916Z to
                                <gloss target="#t_COMKWESTFOR1">COMKWESTFOR</gloss> and COMNAVBASE
                                <gloss target="#t_GTMO1">GTMO</gloss>, April 19; ibid.)</note>
                    </item>
                </list>
            </div>
        </body>
